Subject: [PATCH 6/8] subtle per-section texture + watermarks

Each section now has its own low-opacity background motif AND a giant
faint word-watermark so the eye can tell sections apart without being
distracted. Distinct per section to avoid templatey sameness.

- Plain English: horizontal document-form lines (0.05 opacity cream) +
  "ECP" watermark top-right (0.04 opacity cream, 14-22rem)
- Ethics Gate: brass grid-ledger (existing) + "ETHICS" watermark
  bottom-right (0.03 opacity brass, 9-16rem)
- Pipeline: diagonal safety-orange stripes (existing) + "PIPELINE"
  watermark bottom-right (0.03 opacity orange, 10-18rem)
- Levels of Depth: brass blueprint grid (new, 60px cells) + "LEVELS"
  watermark bottom-left (0.03 opacity brass, 10-16rem)

All watermarks use the Archivo Black display font so they read as
bureau-chrome typography, not generic background decoration. Sitting
under the section content via absolute positioning + pointer-events
none.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
